<section class="section" id="page-headers">
  <h2 class="section-head">Page Headers (anchors)</h2>

  <p>Page headers are not new to Bootstrap, but we have included some additional styles and components. The first customization is a class for the SFDC style page header anchor.</p>

  <p>This element is designed to span the full width of the window. Use a .container element to provide padding and set the width. The page headers in this documentation are an example of this usage.</p>

  <p>These page headers are also responsive. Notice that when you narrow the window the text will center align.</p>

  <div class="fn-example">
    <div class="page-header page-header-anchor">
      <h1>ACME Publishing</h1>
      <p>123 Some Street, San Francisco, CA, 93101</p>
    </div>
  </div>
{{#markdown}}
